messages.content:
RCW 49.46.020 (2023):

"An individual shall be deemed an employee of a hiring entity unless the hiring entity establishes that all three of the following conditions are met:

(A) The worker is free from the control and direction of the hiring entity in connection with the performance of the work, both under the contract and in fact;
(B) The worker performs work that is outside the usual course of the hiring entity's business;
(C) The worker is engaged in an independently established trade, occupation, or business of the same nature as that performed for the hiring entity."

